-YOUR DAUGHTER IS A VERY
COURAGEOUS YOUNG LADY.

05:54.876 --> 05:56.094
-LAUREN KNOWS WHAT SHE WANTS,

05:56.747 --> 05:59.010
AND RIGHT NOW SHE WANTS TO
LEARN HOW TO SAVE LIVES.

05:59.620 --> 06:02.753
[BUSTLING, YELLING]

06:13.460 --> 06:14.635
-GIRL: GIVE IT BACK!

06:15.418 --> 06:16.941
COME ON, I MEAN IT!

06:17.072 --> 06:18.508
-ALL RIGHT, HOBIE,
THAT'S ENOUGH.

06:19.161 --> 06:21.511
A RESCUE CAN IS NOT A TOY.

06:21.642 --> 06:25.428
IT'S DESIGNED FOR ONE PURPOSE,
AND THAT'S TO SAVE LIVES.

06:27.474 --> 06:30.390
SOME OF YOU ARE GONNA WANT
TO BECOME LIFEGUARDS ONE DAY,

06:30.520 --> 06:32.392
SO YOU BETTER START RESPECTING
THE TOOLS OF YOUR TRADE.

06:32.522 --> 06:33.480
THAT GOES FOR YOU...

06:33.610 --> 06:35.525
-DON'T DROOL, BUCHANNON.

06:35.656 --> 06:37.397
-WHAT'RE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

06:37.527 --> 06:38.702
I'M NOT DROOLING.

06:41.313 --> 06:42.184
-HOBIE?

06:43.446 --> 06:44.534
-UH, YEAH?

06:45.361 --> 06:46.884
-DID YOU EVEN HEAR
A WORD THAT I SAID?

06:47.015 --> 06:50.105
-YEAH, UM, YOU SAID...

06:54.239 --> 06:55.153
I'M SORRY.

06:55.284 --> 06:56.154
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

06:56.285 --> 06:57.286
-GOOD.

06:58.156 --> 07:00.811
OKAY, EVERYBODY, I'D LIKE TO
INTRODUCE YOU TO LAUREN TAYLOR.

07:00.942 --> 07:02.900
SHE'S JOINING US HERE
FROM PORTLAND, OREGON,

07:03.031 --> 07:05.512
AS PART OF THE JUNIOR
LIFEGUARD EXCHANGE PROGRAM.

07:05.642 --> 07:07.557
-HI, I'M LAUREN.

07:07.688 --> 07:09.733
-HI, UH, I'M HOBIE.

07:09.864 --> 07:11.387
[GIRL SCOFFS]

07:23.138 --> 07:25.270
-DID YOU LOVE THE OCEAN MORE
THAN YOU LOVED YOUR WIFE?

07:25.401 --> 07:26.663
[LAUGHS]

07:26.794 --> 07:28.099
-WHAT?

07:29.013 --> 07:30.493
-I'LL BET YOU DID.

07:32.234 --> 07:33.931
-WELL, I'M AFRAID YOU'D LOSE.

07:34.062 --> 07:35.237
-I DON'T THINK SO.

07:36.368 --> 07:38.545
MITCH, WE HAVE BEEN
OUT FOUR TIMES,

07:39.328 --> 07:43.027
AND EVERY TIME WE GO EAST
OF PACIFIC COAST HIGHWAY

07:43.158 --> 07:45.943
YOU GO INTO WITHDRAWALS
AND WE HAVE TO GET BACK

07:46.074 --> 07:47.684
HERE FOR A QUICK FIX.

07:48.685 --> 07:51.645
-WELL, I'M A SALTWATER
JUNKIE, WHAT CAN I SAY?

07:53.342 --> 07:56.911
-YOU DON'T REALLY
HAVE TO SAY ANYTHING.

08:03.134 --> 08:04.832
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

08:04.962 --> 08:08.618
[SCREECHING TIRES]

08:10.664 --> 08:12.361
[SCREAMS]

08:21.109 --> 08:22.676
[LOUD SPLASH]

08:23.285 --> 08:24.286
-CALL HEADQUARTERS,
TELL THEM WE NEED

08:24.416 --> 08:25.243
BACKUP IN THE WATER RIGHT NOW.

08:25.374 --> 08:26.288
-OKAY!

09:02.106 --> 09:03.455
-HELP!

09:04.631 --> 09:05.936
HELP!

09:11.115 --> 09:12.203
HELP!

09:16.294 --> 09:18.688
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

09:29.699 --> 09:30.657
-HELP!

09:36.706 --> 09:37.968
HELP!

10:25.929 --> 10:28.584
-KMF295, I'VE GOT A VEHICLE
SUBMERGED AND VICTIM ON BOARD.

10:28.715 --> 10:30.760
I NEED PARAMEDICS
ASAP ON THE DOCK.

10:30.891 --> 10:33.763
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE!

10:35.069 --> 10:37.680
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

10:38.420 --> 10:39.247
[COUGHING]

10:39.377 --> 10:40.901
ALL RIGHT, THERE YOU GO.

10:50.084 --> 10:54.001
[SIZZLING]

10:55.219 --> 10:56.133
-WAITER: HERE YOU GO.

10:59.920 --> 11:01.182
-HERE YOU GO, CJ.

11:01.312 --> 11:02.444
-FINALLY.

11:02.574 --> 11:04.011
I'M STARVING.

11:04.707 --> 11:07.884
-THANK GOD THAT WOMAN
IS GONNA BE ALL RIGHT, HUH?

11:08.015 --> 11:09.407
-YEAH, THANKS TO MITCH.

11:09.538 --> 11:11.018
HE'S THE ONE WHO PULLED
HER OUT OF THE CAR.

11:11.148 --> 11:13.194
-HE IS SO GREAT.

11:16.676 --> 11:18.590
-MM, THIS IS SO GOOD!

11:20.244 --> 11:21.463
-CJ, LOOK AT THAT.

11:21.593 --> 11:22.986
IS THAT SWEET?

11:26.816 --> 11:28.470
[WHINING]

11:29.514 --> 11:30.864
-OH, JACKIE, WHAT'S WRONG?

11:30.994 --> 11:32.779
-OH...

11:32.909 --> 11:34.824
I MEAN IT'S NOT LIKE THERE'S
ANYTHING THAT'S REALLY WRONG.

11:34.955 --> 11:36.652
IT'S JUST...

11:36.783 --> 11:39.133
MITCH AND I HAVE BEEN OUT
ABOUT FOUR OR FIVE TIMES NOW

11:39.263 --> 11:41.788
AND IT IS SO GREAT, I MEAN,
I KNOW THAT HE LIKES ME

11:41.918 --> 11:43.877
AND I REALLY LIKE HIM, BUT...

11:44.007 --> 11:44.834
-BUT?

11:44.965 --> 11:46.444
-WELL...

11:46.575 --> 11:48.708
IT'S LIKE EVERY TIME
THAT WE GET A FIRE GOING,

11:49.665 --> 11:51.536
SOMETHING HAPPENS
TO DOUSE THE FLAMES.

11:52.886 --> 11:54.452
YOU KNOW, LIKE THE
FATES DON'T WANT US

11:54.583 --> 11:55.627
TO BE TOGETHER OR SOMETHING?

11:55.758 --> 11:56.933
-THE FATES?

11:57.064 --> 11:57.978
OR SUMMER?

11:58.718 --> 12:00.110
[CHUCKLES]

12:01.155 --> 12:03.766
-SUMMER IS NOT THRILLED THAT
HER MOM IS DATING HER BOSS,

12:03.897 --> 12:04.854
THAT'S FOR SURE.

12:05.594 --> 12:07.248
BUT I TELL YOU, THE
WAY THINGS ARE GOING,

12:07.378 --> 12:08.336
I DON'T THINK SHE'S GONNA HAVE

12:08.466 --> 12:10.033
TO WORRY ABOUT THAT MUCH LONGER.

12:13.384 --> 12:14.342
HEY, CJ...

12:16.083 --> 12:17.693
YOU KNOW MITCH.

12:17.824 --> 12:19.390
I MEAN, YOU TELL ME,
WHAT SHOULD I DO, HUH?

12:20.914 --> 12:23.568
-WELL, YOU'VE DEFINITELY
COME TO THE RIGHT PERSON.

12:23.699 --> 12:25.266
ROMANCE R US.

12:25.396 --> 12:26.223
OKAY...

12:26.354 --> 12:28.748
STEP ONE: YOU HAVE TO...

12:28.878 --> 12:31.272
[CONVERSATION INAUDIBLE
UNDER CROWD NOISE]

12:35.624 --> 12:37.147
-THAT'S AN AWESOME COMPASS.

12:37.278 --> 12:38.670
CAN I SEE IT?
-YEAH.

12:38.801 --> 12:40.760
IT'S REALLY OLD,
BUT IT WORKS GREAT.

12:40.890 --> 12:42.239
MY GRANDPA GAVE IT TO ME.

12:43.066 --> 12:44.938
-I JUST LOVE THE
WAY COMPASSES WORK.

12:45.808 --> 12:47.810
YOU CAN NEVER GET LOST
WHEN YOU HAVE ONE.

12:50.291 --> 12:51.596
-SUMMER: BREAK'S OVER!

12:51.727 --> 12:53.207
OKAY, LET'S GET BACK TO WORK.

12:55.122 --> 12:58.473
ALL RIGHT, LAUREN, YESTERDAY
EVERYBODY TOLD US

12:58.603 --> 13:00.997
THEIR REASON FOR WANTING TO
BECOME A JUNIOR LIFEGUARD

13:01.128 --> 13:02.999
SO WHY DON'T YOU STAND UP
AND TELL US YOUR REASON?

13:03.695 --> 13:07.351
-WELL, UM, I THINK
SAVING SOMEONE ELSE'S LIFE

13:07.482 --> 13:09.092
IS THE BEST THING IN THE WORLD.

13:09.223 --> 13:10.746
I MEAN, IT CHANGES EVERYTHING.

13:10.877 --> 13:12.879
YOU MAKE THE BIGGEST
DIFFERENCE YOU CAN MAKE.

13:13.488 --> 13:15.185
I REALLY WANT TO FEEL THAT.

13:15.316 --> 13:17.057
-THAT'S THE BEST
REASON I'VE HEARD YET.

13:17.187 --> 13:18.798
THANKS, LAUREN.

13:18.928 --> 13:20.756
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY, LET'S
MOVE TO THE HARD PACK

13:20.887 --> 13:22.497
AND PRACTICE
ARTIFICIAL VENTILATION.

13:22.627 --> 13:23.890
EVERYBODY GRAB A PARTNER.

13:24.020 --> 13:26.370
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

13:28.242 --> 13:29.678
-HEY, I PICKED HER FIRST!

13:32.115 --> 13:34.030
-HOBIE: DON'T WORRY, I'LL SAVE
YOU FROM THESE WANNABES.

13:34.161 --> 13:35.989
[KIDS LAUGHING]

13:36.119 --> 13:37.468
MY NAME'S HOBIE.

13:37.599 --> 13:39.296
-HOBIE-WAN-KENOBI!

13:39.819 --> 13:41.559
-AT YOUR SERVICE,
PRINCESS LAUREN.

13:44.736 --> 13:46.695
-SUMMER: ALL RIGHT,
VICTIMS ON YOUR BACKS.

13:48.871 --> 13:51.613
[GROANING]
-HALF DROWNED!

13:51.743 --> 13:53.136
DELIRIOUS!

13:53.267 --> 13:56.487
ONLY THE PRINCESS LAUREN
CAN SAVE HOBIE-WAN!

13:56.618 --> 14:01.362
-ALL RIGHT, A, B, C, B, A.

14:01.492 --> 14:02.754
-STANDS FOR?

14:02.885 --> 14:04.756
-AIRWAY, BREATHING,
CIRCULATION,

14:04.887 --> 14:06.019
BLEEDING, ASSESSMENT.

14:06.149 --> 14:08.108
HEAD TILT, CHIN LOW.

14:19.771 --> 14:21.425
-GOOD, LAUREN, THAT'S EXCELLENT.

14:35.657 --> 14:36.745
-HOW'S LITTLE LEAGUE GOING?

14:38.573 --> 14:40.009
-UNTIL NOW, PRETTY UNEVENTFUL.

14:41.054 --> 14:42.011
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

14:44.144 --> 14:45.885
-SEE THAT LITTLE GIRL
DOWN THERE WITH HOBIE?

14:47.060 --> 14:48.539
SHE GOT ENROLLED TODAY.

14:51.455 --> 14:52.587
-AW, SHE'S CUTE.

14:53.849 --> 14:55.285
AND LUCKY!

14:55.416 --> 14:56.721
WHO PULLED THE STRINGS
TO GET HER IN LATE?

14:57.635 --> 14:59.289
-WELL, SHE'S
ANYTHING BUT LUCKY.

15:00.160 --> 15:01.944
SHE GOT IN THROUGH THE
MAKE-A-WISH FOUNDATION.

15:02.075 --> 15:03.424
-MAKE-A-WISH?

15:04.729 --> 15:05.861
DON'T THEY HELP KIDS WHO-

15:05.992 --> 15:07.994
-WHO ARE CHRONICALLY
AND TERMINALLY ILL.

15:08.690 --> 15:11.127
MATT, THAT LITTLE GIRL'S
GOT APLASTIC ANEMIA.

15:13.869 --> 15:15.349
SHE'S GOT LESS THAN
A YEAR TO LIVE.

15:16.872 --> 15:18.395
HER WISH SHE WANTED GRANTED

15:18.526 --> 15:20.136
WAS TO LEARN HOW TO
BECOME A LIFEGUARD.

15:22.922 --> 15:24.227
-DO THE OTHER KIDS KNOW?

15:26.186 --> 15:27.274
-NO.

15:28.057 --> 15:30.407
SHE SAID SHE DOESN'T WANT TO
BE TREATED ANY DIFFERENTLY.

15:36.631 --> 15:39.460
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

15:42.680 --> 15:44.465
-SUMMER: GROUP A, GO!

15:45.596 --> 15:47.163
GROUP B, GO!

15:48.948 --> 15:51.646
[KIDS YELLING]

16:13.842 --> 16:16.149
-WOW, WHERE YOU GUYS GOING?

16:16.279 --> 16:18.064
-I WISH I KNEW.

16:18.194 --> 16:21.415
JACKIE INSISTED IT WAS
HER TURN TO PLAN THE DATE.

16:21.545 --> 16:22.546
-THE WEDDING DATE?

16:23.243 --> 16:24.461
-VERY FUNNY.

16:24.592 --> 16:25.767
JACKIE AND I ARE FRIENDS,

16:25.897 --> 16:27.334
WE'RE NOT, UH, YOU KNOW.

16:27.464 --> 16:28.944
-HOBIE: WHAT?
-MITCH: WE'RE NOT...

16:29.597 --> 16:31.164
PASSIONATE WITH EACH OTHER.

16:31.294 --> 16:32.643
-DEFINE PASSIONATE.

16:32.774 --> 16:34.384
-OH, JUST KEEP PUMPING IRON.

16:36.386 --> 16:39.172
-IS IT WHEN YOUR
LIPS TOUCH HERS

16:39.302 --> 16:41.783
AND YOU GET THIS TINGLING
FEELING ALL OVER YOUR BODY

16:41.913 --> 16:43.176
AND EVERY TIME YOU
THINK ABOUT HER

16:43.306 --> 16:44.786
YOU FEEL THAT EXACT SAME WAY?

16:46.614 --> 16:48.442
-WHY ARE YOU ASKING ALL THIS?

16:48.572 --> 16:51.488
-BECAUSE, I THINK I FEEL
PASSIONATE ABOUT A GIRL

16:51.619 --> 16:52.968
I MET TODAY AT JUNIOR GUARDS.

16:53.490 --> 16:54.970
I CAN'T STOP THINKING ABOUT HER!

16:55.536 --> 16:56.928
AND IF I FEEL LIKE...

16:57.059 --> 16:59.540
IF I DON'T PUMP IRON OR
SOMETHING I'LL GO CRAZY.

17:00.367 --> 17:01.411
-A-HA.

17:01.977 --> 17:03.587
SO WHO IS SHE?

17:03.718 --> 17:04.719
SOMEONE NEW?

17:04.848 --> 17:06.415
-HER NAME IS LAUREN.

17:07.069 --> 17:09.070
LAUREN TAYLOR.

17:10.811 --> 17:11.943
-YOU KNOW, HOBSTER,
I THINK WE SHOULD

17:12.074 --> 17:13.597
SLOW DOWN A LITTLE BIT HERE.

17:13.728 --> 17:15.295
-COME ON, DAD.

17:15.425 --> 17:17.165
YOU'VE GIVEN ME
ALL THE TALKS ABOUT

17:17.297 --> 17:19.646
"SOON YOU'LL BE FEELING
FEELINGS," AND EVERYTHING.

17:19.777 --> 17:21.214
JUST GIVE ME A BREAK, OKAY?

17:21.344 --> 17:23.085
-NO, NO, I DON'T MEAN
THAT, IT'S JUST THAT

17:23.215 --> 17:26.175
LAUREN IS FROM OREGON, AND SHE
MIGHT NOT BE HERE THAT LONG.

17:26.696 --> 17:28.351
-YOU DON'T KNOW THAT FOR SURE.

17:28.482 --> 17:30.136
SHE COULD STAY HERE
FOREVER, WHO KNOWS?

17:30.266 --> 17:32.094
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

17:38.318 --> 17:39.971
-WOW, YOU LOOK TERRIFIC.

17:40.102 --> 17:41.364
-WHOA, SO DO YOU.

17:42.322 --> 17:43.453
OH, HI, HOB!

17:43.584 --> 17:44.628
BYE, HOBIE!

17:44.759 --> 17:46.065
-WHERE ARE WE GOING?

17:46.195 --> 17:47.283
-SOMEPLACE YOU'RE GONNA LOVE,

17:47.414 --> 17:48.328
MITCH BUCHANNON.

17:48.458 --> 17:50.156
[GIGGLING] DON'T WAIT UP!

17:51.374 --> 17:52.680
[DOOR CLICKS]
[SCOFFS]

17:56.162 --> 17:57.467
-SUMMER: IT DOESN'T BOTHER ME.

17:58.338 --> 18:00.557
-WHAT, YOUR MOM
DATING THE BOSS?

18:00.688 --> 18:02.777
-DATING HIM IS NOT THE PROBLEM.

18:03.604 --> 18:04.605
-THEN WHAT IS?

18:05.171 --> 18:07.999
-THE PROBLEM IS NOT DATING HIM.

18:08.130 --> 18:09.349
-NOT DATING HIM?

18:11.612 --> 18:14.658
-AFTER THEY BREAK UP
SHE'S GONNA BLAME HERSELF

18:14.789 --> 18:16.965
AND HE IS GONNA FEEL
UNCOMFORTABLE AROUND ME.

18:17.096 --> 18:18.706
-WELL WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
THEY'RE GONNA BREAK UP?

18:19.402 --> 18:21.839
-BECAUSE A RELATIONSHIP
THAT STARTS ONE WAY

18:21.970 --> 18:23.580
DOES NOT END UP
A DIFFERENT WAY.

18:23.711 --> 18:25.800
-WELL, RELATIONSHIPS CAN
ALWAYS GROW AND CHANGE.

18:25.930 --> 18:27.715
-YEAH, FROM BAD TO WORSE.

18:28.368 --> 18:29.847
-WHY ARE YOU BEING SO CYNICAL?

18:29.978 --> 18:31.675
-I'M NOT!

18:31.806 --> 18:33.416
IT'S JUST THAT FRIENDS DON'T
FALL IN LOVE, THAT'S ALL.

18:33.547 --> 18:34.896
-IT HAPPENS ALL THE TIME.

18:35.026 --> 18:36.506
-YEAH, WELL, IT SHOULDN'T.

18:36.637 --> 18:37.681
-WHY NOT?

18:38.291 --> 18:40.684
-BECAUSE IT JUST
COMPLICATES THINGS.

18:41.294 --> 18:42.991
-WELL, I USED TO THINK
IT WAS TOTAL CHEMISTRY.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.601
I MEAN, LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT?

18:44.732 --> 18:46.255
I MEAN, IF IT HAPPENED,

18:46.386 --> 18:47.648
YOU KNEW RIGHT THERE.

18:47.778 --> 18:49.345
-WELL, WHAT DO YOU THINK NOW?

18:50.912 --> 18:52.261
-I THINK IT'S GRADUAL.

18:56.004 --> 18:57.614
YOU GET TO LIKE
A PERSON FIRST.

18:59.399 --> 19:00.965
YOU GET TO KNOW WHO
THEY REALLY ARE.

19:03.229 --> 19:04.926
AND THEN IT JUST
SNEAKS UP ON YOU.

19:09.583 --> 19:11.150
-MATT, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

19:12.281 --> 19:13.543
-I'M COMPLICATING THINGS.

19:14.065 --> 19:16.894
[SOFT MUSIC]

19:34.738 --> 19:39.569
♪ YOU LOOK AT ME
SO DIFFERENT WITH YOUR EYES ♪

19:39.700 --> 19:45.401
♪ THE MYSTERY OF LOVE WE CAN'T DENY NOW

19:47.098 --> 19:50.493
♪ WON'T LET YOU WALK AWAY

19:54.715 --> 19:59.546
-♪ THE BEST OF FRIENDS
I'LL NEVER LET YOU GO ♪

19:59.676 --> 20:01.939
♪ WE CAN'T PRETEND

20:02.070 --> 20:06.205
♪ IT'S TIME TO LET IT SHOW HOW

20:07.118 --> 20:12.428
♪ THESE FEELINGS THAT HAVE GROWN NOW ♪

20:14.648 --> 20:17.259
♪ WHEN YOU CALL MY NAME

20:17.390 --> 20:20.958
♪ I'LL BE THERE

20:24.658 --> 20:26.964
♪ IF YOU FEEL THE SAME

20:27.095 --> 20:31.708
♪ THIS LOVE WE'LL SHARE

