♪ WHEN YOU CALL MY NAME

20:57.256 --> 21:01.129
♪ I'LL BE THERE

21:04.001 --> 21:06.961
[OCEAN WAVES LAPPING SHORE]

21:07.091 --> 21:09.920
[KIDS CHATTER, YELL]

21:17.232 --> 21:21.758
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO! HUSTLE!
-HIT THE WATER, AROUND
THE BUOY AND BACK!

21:21.889 --> 21:23.847
-GRAB A CAN! COME ON!

21:25.849 --> 21:28.809
-I'LL BE ON SHORE
BEFORE SHE ROUNDS THE BUOY.

21:28.939 --> 21:29.897
-YOU OKAY?

21:30.027 --> 21:31.159
[GASPING]
-YEAH.

21:51.440 --> 21:53.224
[GASPING]

21:53.355 --> 21:54.965
[COUGHING]

22:01.494 --> 22:02.408
-LAUREN?

22:02.538 --> 22:03.757
LAUREN!

22:03.887 --> 22:06.107
SUMMER, I NEED BACKUP!

22:13.201 --> 22:17.814
[INTENSE MUSIC]

22:23.516 --> 22:24.604
-HOBIE-WAN...

22:25.474 --> 22:26.606
-DON'T WORRY, PRINCESS,

22:26.736 --> 22:27.694
I GOT YOU.

22:29.609 --> 22:30.653
-ALL RIGHT, HOBIE,
I GOT HER.

22:30.784 --> 22:32.133
-NO, NO, THAT'S OKAY.

22:32.263 --> 22:33.264
I GOT HER.

22:33.395 --> 22:34.657
-ALL RIGHT, SWIM HER IN, OKAY?

22:35.266 --> 22:38.008
[COUGHING, GASPING]

22:52.719 --> 22:53.763
-HOBIE: SIT DOWN.

22:54.634 --> 22:56.157
COME ON, LAUREN,
YOU GOTTA SIT DOWN.

22:56.940 --> 22:58.986
-NO. [COUGHING]

23:00.161 --> 23:01.205
-SIT DOWN!

23:05.514 --> 23:08.996
-IT'S JUST, JUST AN
ALLERGY I GET SOMETIMES.

23:09.126 --> 23:11.172
IT MAKES IT HARD TO
BREATHE, THAT'S ALL.

23:11.912 --> 23:13.174
I'M OKAY, REALLY.

23:13.304 --> 23:15.002
-BRAD, TAKE HER
UP TO HEADQUARTERS

23:15.132 --> 23:16.220
AND CALL HER MOTHER,
ALL RIGHT?

23:16.351 --> 23:18.048
-NO, REALLY, I'M OKAY!

23:18.179 --> 23:19.963
-JUST TO BE ON THE
SAFE SIDE GO WITH BRAD.

23:20.094 --> 23:21.312
THAT'S AN ORDER.

23:22.662 --> 23:23.532
-WOMAN: SHE'S ALL RIGHT.

23:24.838 --> 23:26.013
-HOW DOES IT FEEL?

23:26.970 --> 23:27.841
-WHAT?

23:28.624 --> 23:30.365
-SAVING SOMEONE'S LIFE?

23:30.496 --> 23:32.323
DOES IT FEEL BETTER
THAN ANYTHING?

23:33.237 --> 23:34.325
-SURE.

23:34.456 --> 23:35.457
I GUESS.

23:36.502 --> 23:37.633
IT FEELS GREAT.

23:38.329 --> 23:41.028
-TOMORROW, TELL ME
EVERYTHING ABOUT HOW IT FELT.

23:41.158 --> 23:43.378
[GASPS] EVERYTHING.

23:48.557 --> 23:50.037
-CAN I GO WITH HER?
-SUMMER: NO.

23:50.167 --> 23:52.648
YOU DID YOUR JOB, AND
YOU DID A VERY GOOD JOB.

23:52.779 --> 23:54.433
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

23:54.563 --> 23:55.869
COME ON, YOU GUYS ARE GONNA
SEE EACH OTHER TOMORROW.

23:59.916 --> 24:01.309
-TOO BAD, HOB.

24:01.440 --> 24:03.485
LOOKS LIKE YOUR
GIRLFRIEND'S GONNA WASH OUT.

24:05.966 --> 24:11.362
[SOFT MUSIC]

24:13.582 --> 24:15.018
-JACKIE: HARRY WAS WRONG!

24:15.149 --> 24:16.455
-SUMMER: HARRY WHO?

24:17.020 --> 24:19.936
-BILLY CRYSTAL, YOU KNOW,
IN "HARRY MET SALLY."

24:20.502 --> 24:22.417
HE SAID THAT MEN AND
WOMEN CAN'T BE FRIENDS

24:22.548 --> 24:24.941
WITHOUT ROMANCE
GETTING IN THE WAY.

24:25.464 --> 24:26.900
BUT THE TRUTH IS,

24:27.030 --> 24:29.816
IS THAT FRIENDSHIP GETS
IN THE WAY OF ROMANCE.

24:29.946 --> 24:31.513
-OH, I DON'T THINK THAT'S TRUE.

24:31.644 --> 24:33.820
-TAKE IT FROM ME, IT IS!

24:33.950 --> 24:36.475
-OH YEAH, WELL, TAKE
IT FROM ME, IT ISN'T!

24:38.477 --> 24:39.956
-TAKE IT FROM YOU?

24:40.087 --> 24:41.262
WHY?

24:41.828 --> 24:44.657
-WELL, MATT AND I ARE FRIENDS,

24:45.266 --> 24:48.748
AND LAST NIGHT WE HAD
THE MOST ROMANTIC NIGHT.

24:48.878 --> 24:50.837
[CHUCKLES]
-JACKIE: ROMANTIC?

24:51.446 --> 24:52.926
HOW? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

24:53.056 --> 24:54.928
-ROMANTIC, YOU KNOW, LIKE

24:55.058 --> 24:58.409
RUNNING AND LAUGHING
AND HUGGING AND KISSING.

24:58.540 --> 24:59.889
-OKAY, NO, STOP.

25:00.020 --> 25:01.195
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
ANY MORE OF THIS.

25:01.325 --> 25:03.197
-DON'T WORRY, WE DID.

25:03.327 --> 25:04.503
-SUMMER.

25:05.199 --> 25:06.548
HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?

25:06.679 --> 25:09.029
-I DON'T KNOW, I JUST,
I THINK IT'S KIND OF

25:09.159 --> 25:11.118
BEEN HAPPENING
EVER SINCE WE MET.

25:11.727 --> 25:13.512
-BUT, HONEY,
WHAT ABOUT SLADE?

25:13.642 --> 25:15.775
-SLADE? [GROANS]

25:15.905 --> 25:19.213
JIMMY IS SURFING SOMEWHERE
IN NEW CALEDONIA,

25:19.343 --> 25:21.781
AND NEXT WEEK HE'LL
BE IN AUSTRALIA.

25:21.911 --> 25:24.044
HE'S BEEN GONE SO LONG

25:24.174 --> 25:26.307
I DON'T EVEN KNOW HOW I
FEEL ABOUT HIM ANYMORE.

25:27.656 --> 25:29.876
BUT I DO KNOW HOW
I FEEL ABOUT MATT.

25:30.006 --> 25:33.270
-SUMMER, JIMMY AND MATT
ARE BEST FRIENDS, HONEY.

25:34.358 --> 25:35.534
GETTING BETWEEN
FRIENDS LIKE THAT

25:35.664 --> 25:37.405
CAN BE A HUGE MISTAKE.

25:38.275 --> 25:39.668
-YOU KNOW, WHY IS IT,

25:39.799 --> 25:43.063
WHY IS IT THAT PARENTS,
THEY ALWAYS TRY

25:43.193 --> 25:44.847
TO PROTECT YOU FROM
MAKING THE SAME MISTAKES

25:44.978 --> 25:46.806
THEY'VE PROBABLY ALREADY
MADE THEMSELVES?

25:46.936 --> 25:48.721
-MM-HMM, WHY?
-MM-HMM.

25:49.548 --> 25:50.940
-BECAUSE WE LOVE YOU.

25:51.680 --> 25:53.813
AND IF YOU MAKE
CERTAIN MISTAKES,

25:53.943 --> 25:55.118
I'M GOING TO KILL YOU!

25:55.858 --> 25:56.946
-I GOTTA GO TO WORK.

25:57.077 --> 25:57.991
GOODBYE, MOTHER.

25:58.121 --> 25:59.340
-GOODBYE, DAUGHTER.

26:01.908 --> 26:03.431
HOBIE, YOU'RE LATE!

26:03.562 --> 26:04.519
-SORRY.

26:04.650 --> 26:06.173
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.

26:06.303 --> 26:07.696
WASH UP AND HELP SET
UP THE TABLES, ALL RIGHT?

26:07.827 --> 26:08.828
-CJ: HEY, HOB.

26:09.568 --> 26:11.004
MORNING, HOB.

26:11.134 --> 26:12.396
YO, HOBIE!

26:12.527 --> 26:14.094
[LAUGHING]
WHAT'S UP WITH HOBIE?

26:14.224 --> 26:15.965
-OH, HE'S IN LOVE.

26:16.096 --> 26:18.620
WHAT ELSE COULD MAKE
ANYONE FEEL THAT BAD?

26:19.490 --> 26:21.101
-OH NO...

26:21.231 --> 26:22.581
DON'T TELL ME; WHAT HAPPENED
WITH MITCH LAST NIGHT?

26:23.320 --> 26:25.105
-CJ, IT WAS PERFECT.

26:25.235 --> 26:27.890
YOU KNOW, THE
GONDOLA, THE SUNSET,

26:28.021 --> 26:30.240
THE WINE, OH...

26:30.371 --> 26:31.807
WE KISSED.

26:32.503 --> 26:33.504
-AND?

26:34.636 --> 26:36.029
-HE JUMPED OUT OF THE GONDOLA.

26:37.334 --> 26:38.161
-WHAT?

26:38.292 --> 26:40.250
-IN HIS TUXEDO!

26:40.947 --> 26:42.731
HE SAID IT WAS TO
RESCUE TWO BOYS

26:42.862 --> 26:44.603
WHO WERE MARGINALLY IN TROUBLE.

26:44.733 --> 26:45.734
CJ...

26:45.865 --> 26:47.997
IT WAS A CLEAR GETAWAY.

26:48.128 --> 26:49.390
-ALL RIGHT, THAT'S IT.

26:49.520 --> 26:50.913
TIME TO BRING OUT THE BIG GUNS.

26:51.871 --> 26:53.046
-BIG GUNS?

26:53.176 --> 26:54.308
-HOWITZER'S.

26:54.438 --> 26:55.744
SCORCHED EARTH.

26:55.875 --> 26:56.876
TAKE NO PRISONERS.

26:57.746 --> 26:58.573
-OKAY.

26:58.704 --> 27:00.357
I LIKE THE SOUND OF THIS.

27:00.488 --> 27:01.402
TELL ME MORE.

27:02.838 --> 27:04.057
-LOVER'S COVE.

27:04.187 --> 27:05.275
NORTH OF MALIBU.

27:05.406 --> 27:06.799
-JACKIE: LOVER'S COVE?

27:06.929 --> 27:08.931
[LAUGHING] OH, I LIKE
THE SOUND OF THAT.

27:09.497 --> 27:11.891
-CJ: THERE'S A CHURCH IN THE
HILLS JUST AROUND THE COVE,

27:12.021 --> 27:14.371
AND EVERY HOUR THE
CHURCH BELLS RING

27:14.502 --> 27:15.764
AND ECHO THROUGH THE HILLS.

27:17.461 --> 27:20.813
IT IS THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
SOUND YOU HAVE EVER HEARD.

27:21.422 --> 27:23.119
AND THE LEGEND IS
IF TWO PEOPLE KISS

27:23.250 --> 27:26.340
AND KEEP KISSING UNTIL
THE BELLS STOP RINGING,

27:26.470 --> 27:28.908
THEY'LL BE IN LOVE FOREVER.

27:30.300 --> 27:31.475
WORKED FOR ME.

27:31.606 --> 27:32.694
THREE TIMES.

27:33.303 --> 27:34.696
-THREE TIMES?

27:34.827 --> 27:36.306
CJ, YOU NUT.

27:38.308 --> 27:41.703
[ORCHESTRAL MUSIC]

27:49.232 --> 27:50.538
[SEAGULLS SQUAWK]

28:01.201 --> 28:02.419
-LAUREN, HI.

28:03.594 --> 28:04.944
HOW'S YOUR ALLERGY?

28:05.074 --> 28:06.206
-NOT SO GOOD.

28:07.990 --> 28:10.297
-WELL, THERE'S SOMETHING YOU
CAN TAKE FOR IT, ISN'T THERE?

28:11.428 --> 28:12.603
-NOT REALLY.

28:12.734 --> 28:14.562
-WELL, WHAT I MEAN
IS YOU CAN STILL

28:14.693 --> 28:16.085
DO JUNIOR GUARDS, CAN'T YOU?

28:16.216 --> 28:18.305
-MY MOM'S IN WITH YOUR DAD NOW.

28:19.219 --> 28:21.134
TODAY'S MY LAST DAY.
-WHAT?

28:21.656 --> 28:22.526
THAT'S NOT FAIR!

28:23.310 --> 28:25.355
-THAT'S ONLY CAUSE
TODAY'S ALL CLASSROOM WORK.

28:26.269 --> 28:28.837
I DIDN'T EVEN GET TO SURF,
SKI, OR RIDE A WAVERUNNER.

28:32.406 --> 28:33.407
-LET'S DO IT, THEN.

28:34.234 --> 28:35.148
-WHAT?

28:35.278 --> 28:36.715
-RIDE A WAVERUNNER.

28:37.237 --> 28:38.847
THERE'S A PLACE I WANT
TO TAKE YOU, ANYWAY.

28:39.587 --> 28:41.371
-WHAT KIND OF PLACE?

28:41.502 --> 28:44.026
-A SPECIAL PLACE, BUT WE HAVE
TO GET THERE BEFORE SUNSET.

28:48.117 --> 28:49.771
-OKAY, HOBIE-WAN, TAKE ME THERE.

28:49.902 --> 28:55.037
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

29:02.262 --> 29:04.394
-♪ WHEN YOU'RE WITH ME

29:05.874 --> 29:11.010
♪ FEELS LIKE I'M CHASING THE SUN

29:12.185 --> 29:13.795
♪ FALLING SO DEEP

29:14.622 --> 29:19.105
